subSubSection.paragraph:
(1) [
Areole long; Rs1 from just beyond middle of areole; Rs2 and Rs3 long stalked, from upper distal corner of areole; Rs4 from lower distal corner of cell
] Rs1 and stalk (Rs2+Rs3) long stalked, from before end of cell, areole very long, bound superiorly by stalk (Rs1+(Rs2+Rs3)) and stalk (Rs2+Rs3), inferiorly by Rs (viz. cell) and Rs4, and closed by short anastomosis that from Rs4 reaches stalk (Rs2+Rs3) (Fig. 
7
).

(2) [
Areole short; Rs1 from 4/5 length of areole; stalk of Rs2 and Rs3 shortly stalked with Rs4, from end of areole
] Rs1 and Rs2' stalked, from before end of cell, Rs2' free from bifurcation with Rs1 for short tract, then anastomosed and cojoined into short stalk ((Rs2
"+Rs3)+Rs4"
) which then separates into long stalk (Rs2"+Rs3) and Rs4", areole thus short, bound superiorly by stalk (Rs1+Rs2') and Rs2', and inferiorly by Rs (viz. cell) and Rs4' (Fig. 
8
).

